<br>
When I go to Hate without my pet, I'm not having fun.  I'm ineffective.  A poor excuse for a (much) lower level wizard.  If you're not allowing pets, why bring a mage?  Bring another warrior.  Hell, at least he may see some Indicolite drop.  In 3 Hate raids I've only seen 1 piece of Apothic drop, because the Revs are too deep, and by the time you get to them everyone (mages included) want to go to bed.  But that's another matter.<br>
<br>
Can it not be argued that a Mage without their pet is the weakest class in the game?  We contribute the least.<br>
<br>
What frustrates me is that others dictate to us how we can play our class.  This is wrong.  We know how to control our pets.  The raid leader had a bad experience in Blackburrow, and now he won't raid with pets.  But the worst part is we follow him.  We accept his ignorance of our class, our pets, and our effectiveness, and follow for the lure of Apothic.<br>
