<br>
Will I allow pets? Only for the new boss mobs, and 'Stro.  Why?  because I don't want ANYONE to end up having to put up with the crap from the rest of the raid if ANYTHING bad happens and is PERCEIVED to have been caused by the pet.  Also, being a mage myself, a LOT of mages don't know proper control of their pets (i.e. to keep from breaking mezzes, etc).  I'm sorry, you may say you can do it, but until you PROVE to me, and I can TRUST you, I wouldn't let you.<br>
<br>
Also, since it's someone elses raid, you have the option of going or not going, and abiding by THEIR rules.  If you wanna do a riad that allows pets, and they don't want to come, more power to them.  It's your raid.<br>
<br>
People need to learn that when on someone elses raid, you're agreeing to abide by their rules (be they posted on a message board at signup, being told in /ooc, /shout, whatever, etc).  You have NO RIGHT AT ALL to complain if they say no pets.  Go up, do what you can do, and be happy to be there.  Opposite is true when you run a raid and say &quot;We'll gladly allow you Enchanters, Mages, Druids, Shaman, Necros, etc. use your pets, you're responsible for them.&quot;  If you tell people at sign up for your raid those are the rules, and they still wanna come, that's their decision.  But I, personally, wouldn't want to risk OTHERS lives because of some fubar pathing problem, gfluxing to second floor and pet bringing back the whole thing before you can invis, etc.  Have some respect for those people too.  Things happen, we all don't blame them, but until Verant fixes the problems inherent with pets in general (pathing being the biggest), you MUSt understand people's trepidation.<br>
<br>
