And Meneldil, I already do other things (since I'm so ineffective offensively).  I make sure I'm the monk's supplier.  Woohoo.  And the DS the mobs have is the wizard DS, not mage, so it's a joke.  Annuling will frequently dispell one of the debuffs someone slapped on the mob and piss them off.  And that debuff is more important than dispelling the weak DS.  Doing other things can be fun, but for 8-12 hours?  On every raid?  Remember, since you're dead weight, odds are your group never gets the xp, either.  Yes, Hate is about loot not xp, but xp is nice every now and then.<br>
<br>
Marthisdil, you're right.  It's their raid; I must abide by their rules.  However, since they do not respect mages, do you think they post NO PETS on the signup board?  Of course not.  I don't find that out until after I've spent 2 hours waiting in SRo, and another hour or two waiting for the break-in to finish.  Only THEN am I told, via shout, NO PETS.  I just wasted 4 hours because mages are overlooked.  Gee, maybe we're overlooked because we suck?  Maybe we suck because we don't have any pets?  Now I get to look forward to spending the rest of the night as a poor excuse for a wizard, just dead weight really.  How fun.  I can't even leave lest I look like an @#%$.<br>
<br>
And the plot thickens Marthisdil.  I mentioned the upcoming Hate raid.  It's being organized by MY guild.  Yet still, my own guild will not let me have my pet.  My own guild.  It’s not that they don’t trust me, they don’t trust mages.  To make it even more interesting, it's being organized by my GF, who sits not 10 feet away from me when we play EQ.  Because so many cowardly, ignorant fools have said they won't go if pets are allowed, she has not choice but to prohibit pets on the raid.  I suppose the upside is that this time I know it in advance.<br>
<br>
Marthisdil, I'm very disappointed that you continue to promote the false rumor that pets in Hate (at the safe wall) are bad.  People such as yourself are the very reason we have this problem to begin with.  BTW, if feel that way, don't bother summoning them for the mini-bosses either.  They're not much tougher than the regular mobs, just more hps and hit a little harder.<br>
<br>
